                  jsx.ui.event.Change

public final class Change
extends Widget.Event<OnChange>

A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org

Constructor Detail

Change

public Change(Component target)

Constructs an event of this type.

This constructor simply invokes the default constructor of the superclass and sets its configurable property Widget.Event.TARGET to the argument component.

Note that, this constructor does not change the configurable properties Source.Event.BUBBLE and Source.Event.UPDATE of this event object.

Parameters:
target - The component where the mouse is clicked. It may be different from the source widget which has is firing the event.
Since:
1.0
